//help issues Find and improve your location\'s accuracy Sometimes Google Maps might have trouble finding where you are located. If the GPS location of your blue dot on the map is inaccurate or the blue dot is not showing up, here are some things you can do to help fix the problem. See your current location on the map 1. On your android phone or tablet, open the Google Maps app. If you don\'t have the app, download it from the Play Store. 2. you\'ll see a blue dot, which shows where you are. If you don\'t see a blue dot, go to the bottom and tap your location. Turn on high-accuracy mode 1. Open the Google Maps app then open the Settings app. 2. Tap Location. 3. At the top, switch location on. 4. Tap Mode > High accuracy. If this article isn\'t helpful, send your feedback helping us to improve it. Change or reset passsword You can change your password for security reasons or reset it if you forget it. Change your password 1. Go to the settings of Parkino app. 2. Tap password. 3. Enter your new password then tab OK. Reset your password Charge your points You should\'t let your points less than 10 points to guarantee that you can always be able to reserve garages anytime. To charge your points : 1. Tab the menu button of Parkino app. 2. choose charge. 3. Select the package of points you want to charge. 4. Write your credit card data. 5. Tab Pay button. Add or remove RFID card You have the ability to use more than one RFID card, so you can remove one or add one anytime. Add RFID card 2. Choose My Cards. 3. Tab the addition button down there. 4. Scan the QR code on the RFID card with the camera of your phone/tablet. 5. Parkino app will detect your card automatically and add it to your cards. Remove RFID card 3. Swipe right or left the card you want to delete. 4. write your password for confirmation. GPS Not Enabled Open Location Settings Cancel
